249
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:03,240
Let's go to the mall. To get dinner.

250
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,930
The mall.

251
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:09,130
Right.

252
00:16:11,230 --> 00:16:15,930
Everything looked delicious. Dinner will be a tough choice.

253
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:17,990
Can we also get a cake?

254
00:16:17,990 --> 00:16:20,990
Of course. But after we get your present.

255
00:16:22,570 --> 00:16:26,460
- I can't seem to find anything I like. 
- What?

256
00:16:26,460 --> 00:16:31,030
I mean, you've already given me everything that I wanted.

257
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:33,310
Seriously? I don't think so, though.

258
00:16:33,310 --> 00:16:39,950
You gave me the matching keychain at the aquarium, and stationery when we were kids, too.

259
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:46,780
And you're content with that?

260
00:16:48,060 --> 00:16:50,180
It's not only the material stuff.

261
00:16:50,180 --> 00:16:54,850
Ever since we started dating, you've given me nothing but happiness every day.

262
00:16:57,060 --> 00:17:01,200
The one I want is already right in front of me.

263
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,970
Koyori...

264
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:13,810
There's still something I haven't given you yet.

265
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:17,540
Like...

266
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:21,990
a ring.

267
00:17:30,670 --> 00:17:34,290
Were you trying to measure my ring size?

268
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,200
I was.

269
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:43,770
I wanted to secretly get you one for your birthday, but I didn't know if you'd like it.

270
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:49,340
Then I figured we'd go get it together, but nothing caught your eye, so I started to panic.

271
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:50,970
Sorry about that.

272
00:17:52,130 --> 00:17:56,010
So what do we do now? Shall we go back to the jewelry shop?

273
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:10,170
Instead of getting it now, I'd prefer to wear it when I get married someday.

274
00:18:15,610 --> 00:18:17,250
Is that so?

275
00:18:20,650 --> 00:18:23,660
In that case, let's go buy the cake and head home.

276
00:18:23,660 --> 00:18:25,900
Yeah, sounds good.

277
00:18:33,430 --> 00:18:34,980
Your fried egg looks good.

278
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:37,370
Huh? Y-You want my egg?

279
00:18:37,370 --> 00:18:40,010
- May I? 
 - No, not mine.

280
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:42,710
- No? 
 - You really like eggs, don't you?

281
00:18:42,710 --> 00:18:45,090
- Yes, ma'am. I love my proteins. 
 - I see.

282
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:46,730
Here, have some.

283
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:48,780
That's rare, coming from you.

284
00:18:48,780 --> 00:18:50,540
Oh, thanks.

285
00:18:50,540 --> 00:18:52,720
- Looks delicious. 
 - Thank you very much!

286
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:56,400
Wow, cookies.

287
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:59,850
- They look so fancy. 
 - I'll take a bite.

288
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:02,740
- It's delicious. 
 - Glad to hear that.

289
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,960
Thank you for the cookies.

290
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:08,700
I need to ask you guys a favor.

291
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:11,170
Wait, that's why you gave us cookies?

292
00:19:11,170 --> 00:19:13,830
Oh no, I ate them.

293
00:19:13,830 --> 00:19:18,680
Actually, I'm getting married.

294
00:19:26,470 --> 00:19:29,510
Hoshi, wanna check out that new bar under the bridge?

295
00:19:29,510 --> 00:19:31,380
Ah, that one. Let's go check it out.

296
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:32,660
Congratulations!

297
00:19:32,660 --> 00:19:35,310
I really appreciate it, Enomoto.

298
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:37,310
Will you be holding a wedding ceremony?

299
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:40,590
Yes. That's why I'm asking you guys a favor.

300
00:19:40,590 --> 00:19:44,700
No, you want us to do some lame performance at your wedding?

301
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:46,480
She's your ex, for goodness' sake!

302
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:48,370
- Ms. Hoshi! 
 - Sorry about that.

303
00:19:48,370 --> 00:19:50,230
- Are you okay? 
 - Have some water, Ms. Hoshi.

304
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:51,850
Thanks.

305
00:19:51,850 --> 00:19:53,280
What do mean by "your ex"?

306
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:55,640
- We don't have to go there. 
 - Oops, sorry.

307
00:19:55,640 --> 00:20:00,750
We plan to do away with the reception, and just have a small ceremony with close relatives.

308
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:04,310
- But we may hold an after-partyー 
 - And we're supposed to do the lame performance there?

309
00:20:04,310 --> 00:20:06,450
Let's forget the performance, shall we?

310
00:20:06,450 --> 00:20:11,010
What I need help with is handling the reception desk, emceeing at the after-party,

311
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:13,540
and maybe prepping some bingo-game prizes.

312
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:18,290
In other words, you're asking for our help at the after-party, right?

313
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:23,230
Of course, I'll repay you all, and I know it's a troublesome favor.

314
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:26,110
But I hope you can help.

315
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:31,030
Sure, we'll help.

316
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:35,320
I'll be there for you!

317
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:37,410
I'll go since Hoshi agreed.

318
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:42,140
Congratulations on your wedding.

319
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:45,270
Thank you.

320
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:50,660
- I'll leave the delivery schedule to you. 
 - Got it.

321
00:20:50,660 --> 00:20:52,670
- See you. 
 - Bye.

322
00:20:59,630 --> 00:21:02,430
- Thanks for agreeing to help. 
 - No worries.

323
00:21:02,430 --> 00:21:07,660
By the way, I forgot to ask. Who is your wife-to-be?

324
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:10,400
Did I not tell you?

325
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:12,460
- It's Saito. 
 - Huh?

326
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:14,840
That Saito?

327
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:18,150
Yeah, we had a lot going on, so.

328
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:21,690
I see...

329
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:27,210
Sorry, Hoshi.

330
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:29,090
Why are you apologizing?

331
00:21:29,090 --> 00:21:32,520
You ought to have gotten married before I did.

332
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:35,930
You're sorry you got ahead of me? How condescending.

333
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:37,900
- No, you're wrong. 
 - Oh yeah?

334
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:43,620
Since he's your childhood friend, I just figured you'd skip the whole dating step.

335
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:49,140
Of course we did think about that, but...

336
00:21:49,140 --> 00:21:51,060
But?

337
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:54,990
As childhood friends, we may have known each other for a long time.

338
00:21:54,990 --> 00:21:58,420
But our time together as a couple has only just started.

